  "title": "Electrical Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Troubleshoot Plant Monitoring & Control System and Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition systems.</li><li>Perform troubleshooting of electrical controls system.</li><li>Upkeep proper filling system for maintenance records.</li><li>Scheduling of preventive maintenance works.</li><li>Managing all maintenance breakdown and ensure all faults are attended.</li><li>Supervise onsite installations, testing and commissioning.</li><li>Plan and co-ordinate with subcon and team members to execute all master schedules.</li><li>Conduct routine inspection of the premises.</li><li>Site meeting and liaising client.</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Relevant University Degree in Electrical & Electronics or Electronics & Communication Engineering and equivalent with 3 years’ experience or relevant Diploma in Electrical & Electronics / Electronics & Communication Engineering / M&E Co-ordination and equivalent with 6 years’ experience.</li></ul>",
